The paper deals with facial action unit detection, which is a problem in computer vision. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a semi-supervised learning framework, which involves training a model with both labeled and unlabeled data, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of adversarial learning, which falls under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper evaluates its method on benchmark datasets, which falls under cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper discusses the challenges of detecting facial expressions in unconstrained environments, which falls under cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction).
